### Event Gateway — example requests
### Works with the VS Code "REST Client" extension or IntelliJ's built-in HTTP Client.
### Start both services first: docker compose up (or ./gradlew bootRun in each project)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### Submit a CREDIT event
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "evt-001",
  "accountId": "acct-123",
  "type": "CREDIT",
  "amount": 150.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-05-15T14:02:11Z",
  "metadata": {
    "source": "mainframe-batch",
    "batchId": "B-9042"
  }
}

### Resubmit the same eventId — idempotent, 200 OK with duplicate=true, balance unchanged
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "evt-001",
  "accountId": "acct-123",
  "type": "CREDIT",
  "amount": 150.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-05-15T14:02:11Z"
}

### Submit a second event with an EARLIER timestamp (arrives out of order)
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "evt-000",
  "accountId": "acct-123",
  "type": "DEBIT",
  "amount": 20.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-05-15T10:00:00Z"
}

### Get a single event by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/evt-001

### List events for the account — ordered by eventTimestamp ascending (evt-000 first, despite arriving second)
GET {{baseUrl}}/events?account=acct-123

### Event that does not exist — 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/does-not-exist

### Validation error — missing required field (eventId)
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountId": "acct-123",
  "type": "CREDIT",
  "amount": 10.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-05-15T14:02:11Z"
}

### Validation error — unknown event type
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "evt-bad-type",
  "accountId": "acct-123",
  "type": "REFUND",
  "amount": 10.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "eventTimestamp": "2026-05-15T14:02:11Z"
}

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### OpenAPI spec (JSON)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v3/api-docs

### Swagger UI (open in a browser, not usable from the HTTP client itself)
GET {{baseUrl}}/swagger-ui/index.html
